article_title: Republican Congress Sets Low Expectations for 2016 Lawmaking
article_text:
WASHINGTON—After productivity and compromise on some key issues in 2015, Republican leaders in Congress are sending a message about next year: Don’t expect us to replicate it.

Lawmakers this year agreed to a $1.15 trillion bill to fund the government through September and reached major, unexpected deals with the White House on education, highways, trade and a bundle of other issues.

But they are already setting lower...
